description:
WHY: Replace the execute/query sprawl (13 async execute/query entries + 9 blocking twins) with four operation families over a private OperationCore dispatch layer atop W1-T1's ConnectionCore. This API becomes a BLOCKING SemVer contract at 0.3.0, so it must be deliberate + lose nothing. WORKED DESIGN IS AUTHORITATIVE: docs/API_DESIGN.md (the full spec — Params/Query/Execute/Batch/Registration + Rows/ExecuteOutcome/BatchOutcome/RegistrationOutcome, retained low-level surface, BlockingConnection mirror, examples, and the old→new "nothing lost" map across all 24 capability groups). Built from the verified capability inventory + the Rust-DB precedent survey.

SIGNATURES (builder-taking forms; bare query/execute/execute_many take (sql, params)):
  query_with(&mut self, cx:&Cx, q:Query) -> Result<Rows>;
  execute_with(&mut self, cx:&Cx, e:Execute) -> Result<ExecuteOutcome>;
  execute_many_with(&mut self, cx:&Cx, b:Batch) -> Result<BatchOutcome>;
  register_query(&mut self, cx:&Cx, r:Registration) -> Result<RegistrationOutcome>;
Distinct borrowed request/result types per family (no invalid combos: batch rows ≠ scalar binds; fetch/LOB policy only on Query; CQN only on Registration). Prefer borrowed params + owned convenience From conversions. Validated NonZero sizes. BlockingConnection mirrors 1:1.

SINGLE OP-DEADLINE (verified gap; API_DESIGN.md principle 7): relative timeouts use Duration, translated ONCE into a single ABSOLUTE deadline carried in the op/cursor context across EVERY round-trip of the logical op — the initial call plus all Rows::next_batch/collect continuations and LOB chunks — NEVER re-armed per round-trip. Fixes the current per-call model (timeout_ms:u32 applied per call, lib.rs:1911/2981, so an N-batch fetch can run up to N× the budget). A tighter Cx deadline wins; the post-timeout drain runs under its own bounded budget (W1-T2).

SUBSUMED SPRAWL (async Connection, crates/oracledb/src/lib.rs): execute_query(:2469), _collect(:2530), _with_timeout(:2561), _with_binds(:2578), _with_binds_and_timeout(:2600), query(:2629), query_named(:2659), query_named_with_timeout(:2675), _with_bind_rows(:2694), _with_bind_rows_and_options(:2711, real core + ORA-932/1007 refetch :2736), _with_bind_rows_and_timeout(:2941), _with_bind_rows_options_and_timeout(:2959), execute_query_for_registration(:1869) + BlockingConnection twins(:5296-5525). The fetch/paging family (fetch_rows* :3053, for_each_row_ref :3281, define_and_fetch :3377, fetch_cursor :3418) STAYS (distinct low-level capability).

ACCEPTANCE: the four families cover every prior capability (old→new mapping table in the PR); invalid states unrepresentable; harness/run.sh diff stays green (anti-drift guard).
TESTS: the nothing-lost mapping table proven by tests exercising each of the 24 capability groups; doc-tests for the worked examples; conformance (harness/run.sh diff) green.
DEPS: W0-T5 (ledger), W1-T1, W1-T2. Feeds W1-T4, W1-T8, W1-T9, W2-T1.

WHY (polish round 1 — explicit test-coverage requirement): the qualification suite has conformance (harness/run.sh diff vs the python suite), the oraclemcp contract suite (W3-E7.3), and deterministic suites (E3-E6), but NO driver-native end-to-end scripts that exercise the shipped public API against a live Oracle container with VERBOSE PER-STEP LOGGING. After implementation we must be able to run one set of scripts and SEE, step by step, that everything works.

SCOPE: a set of e2e scripts (e.g. tests/e2e/*.rs run with --ignored, or scripts/e2e/*.sh) each emitting detailed structured logs — phase, elapsed, rows/bytes, cursor id, pool state counts, connection disposition — with secrets REDACTED (reuse the W1-T6 redaction policy). Cover, end to end:
- connect/auth + TLS/TCPS handshake (each supported TLS mode from docs/SUPPORT.md);
- the four families: query (single + multi-batch fetch honoring ONE op-deadline), query_one/opt/all, execute (+ OUT/RETURNING/implicit results), execute_many (array DML + batch_errors), register_query (CQN round-trip);
- pool LIVE stress: N concurrent acquires, acquire-timeout, cancel-DURING-acquire (assert no leak/double-hand), reaper expiry/ping, graceful + forced close — logging PoolState counts at each step;
- cancel/recovery: a real call timeout → BREAK → drain → REUSE the same connection (assert Ready, not Dead) with the recovery phase logged;
- LOB streaming read/write (multi-chunk, logged per chunk); transaction commit/rollback; the blocking facade mirror of the above.

ACCEPTANCE: every script runs green against the container and PRINTS a legible, step-by-step trace; a failure is diagnosable from the log alone; secrets never appear (redaction test over the captured logs). Runs are #[ignore]/manual + wired into the soak + release-qualification tiers.
TESTS: this bead IS the e2e test layer. Pair with the unit/property/DPOR layers (E1-E6) and the conformance diff.
DEPS: W2-T1 (the migrated API) — inherited via the W3-E7 parent chain. Exercises W1-T2/T3/T6/T7. Feeds W4-T2 (run definitively on the RC SHA).
